
## Kotlin/Android Development Conventions

### Code Quality Stack
- `./gradlew detekt` — Kotlin static analysis
- `./gradlew ktlintCheck` — Kotlin formatting
- `./gradlew lint` — Android lint checks
- All must pass before committing feat:/fix: changes

### Kotlin Coding Conventions
- Use `sealed class`/`sealed interface` for restricted hierarchies
- Prefer `data class` for DTOs, `value class` for type-safe wrappers
- Use `Result<T>` or custom sealed class for operation outcomes
- Coroutines: always specify Dispatcher, use structured concurrency
- Null safety: avoid `!!` — use `?.let {}`, `?:`, or `requireNotNull()`

### Compose Testing Patterns
```kotlin
@get:Rule
val composeTestRule = createComposeRule()

@Test
fun displayTitle() {
    composeTestRule.setContent {
        MyScreen(title = "Test Title")
    }
    composeTestRule.onNodeWithText("Test Title").assertIsDisplayed()
}

@Test
fun clickButton() {
    val onClick = mockk<() -> Unit>(relaxed = true)
    composeTestRule.setContent {
        MyButton(onClick = onClick)
    }
    composeTestRule.onNodeWithContentDescription("Submit").performClick()
    verify { onClick() }
}
```

### Timber Logging Conventions
```kotlin
// Use Timber with tags
Timber.d("[%s] %s", TAG, "Action with context: $value")
Timber.w("[%s] %s", TAG, "Unexpected state: $description")
Timber.e(exception, "[%s] %s", TAG, "What failed")

// Plant in Application.onCreate()
if (BuildConfig.DEBUG) {
    Timber.plant(Timber.DebugTree())
}
```

### Android Lifecycle Rules
- Collect Flows with `repeatOnLifecycle(Lifecycle.State.STARTED)`
- Never pass Activity/Fragment context to ViewModel
- Use `viewModelScope` for ViewModel coroutines
- Use `lifecycleScope` for UI-related coroutines in Activity/Fragment
- Cancel work in `onCleared()` / `onDestroy()`

### Deploy
- Use /deploy-android skill for APK/AAB build + signing + distribution
